3 June 2026

BUILD AREA for SNN environment

snn-stable refers to a stable version of the SNN env meant for production jobs
Please request that we tag a version of the SNN env

ssn-dev includes an editable SuperNNova pakage under development
When a version of the environment is to be tagged, we should use snn-stable to denote that.

BUILD SCRIPTS

build-snn.sh  
builds snn-stable, moving the symlink if the build is successful

snn-dev/build-snn-dev.sh  
builds the latest dev version and move they "dev" symlink if the build is succsesful

SETUP SCRIPTS

source $CFS/lsst/groups/TD/snn/snn-dev/setup-snn-dev.sh
sets up the "dev" environment 



